@startuml vcu_vehicle_mode_to_isg_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title VCU Vehicle Mode To ISG State Signal Flow\n(VCU vehicle-mode + fuel-battery context -> ISG state publication)

participant "VCU\nvehicle-mode producer" as VCU #E8F7E8
participant "Fuel/Battery source" as FB #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state\nspeed / drive state" as Veh #F4F7FB
participant "ISG\nidle-stop-go owner" as ISG #FFF4CC
participant "Powertrain observers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== ISG Inputs ==

VCU -> ISG : frmVehicleModeMsg\nDriveMode / PowertrainState
FB -> ISG : frmFuelBatteryStateMsg\nBatterySoc / ChargingState
Veh -> ISG : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState / VehicleSpeed
activate ISG
ISG -> ISG : normalize stale fuel-battery / vehicle inputs
ISG -> ISG : if PowertrainState == 0 -> ISG off
ISG -> ISG : else derive RestartReady / RecuperationLvl
note right of ISG
Representative outputs
- IsgState
- RestartReady
- RecuperationLvl
end note

== ISG Publish ==

ISG -> Obs : frmIsgStateMsg
ISG -> Obs : traceable ISG state /\nrestart / regen visibility
deactivate ISG

note over VCU, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. VCU publishes vehicle mode and powertrain state
2. ISG combines that with fuel-battery and vehicle-speed context
3. ISG derives restart readiness and recuperation level
4. Powertrain observers verify idle-stop-go behavior
end note

@enduml
